3rd Party Synd. Remarks: Price Reduced! Located in the Maxwell Park area of Oakland, this single level home just began its second century of life. And it's definitely a step back in time...to a simpler era, when building materials were crafted by artisans and installed by master carpenters. For starters, there are original hardwood floors throughout most of the home. The dining room has the 1920s written all over it, with a dramatic coffered ceiling, custom wall panels and a built-in buffet / dining hutch. The custom wood-framed picture windows add elegance and comfort to the living room, while the fireplace adds cozy winter-time warmth. The large open country kitchen is just off the dining room and features gas cooking. There's also an interior laundry & utility room on the opposite side of the kitchen. While most of the home retains its classic 1920s style and allure, the home has some modern conveniences, too, including central heat. There's also a long driveway on the left side of the house, with ample room to park several cars. And a portion of the former garage still stands at the end of the driveway, which, with a little extra work, could even serve as a handy carport for the time being.
Confidential Remarks: Price Reduced! Vacant, please leave a card & lock up tight when you're done. Include POF, lender letter & signed disclosure cover sheet with your offer & email to rjherman@HomeSection.com. For disclosures, click on link in Attached Docs or copy/paste this URL: bit.ly/55thAveDisc. Sellers had inspections in early 2022, which are included with the disclosures. (Note that the Roof Doctors report said the roof had 10 years left but gave an absurdly high estimate for seemingly minor repairs, so the sellers had another roof inspection, which came in 90% lower). The home is priced for an as-is sale, as most updated Maxwell Park homes sell for several hundred thousand more. The seller already has a sewer compliance certificate. Oakland also has a sidewalk ordinance and the seller's 2022 sidewalk inspection quoted $4,755 to perform required sidewalk repairs. If buyer takes responsibility for the sidewalk, they have 120 days after COE to complete the work. Oakland's City Transfer Tax is $15/$1,000, which is customarily split 50/50 between buyer & seller. To access the backyard, use the key to the laundry room door or the padlock on chain link driveway gate (both keys are on a hook inside the tall white kitchen cabinet -- be sure to lock gate & put keys back when done!)

For starters, there are original hardwood floors throughout most of the home. The dining room has the 1920s written all over it, with a dramatic coffered ceiling, custom wall panels and a built-in buffet / dining hutch. The custom wood-framed picture windows add elegance and comfort to the living room, while the fireplace adds cozy winter-time warmth. The large open country kitchen is just off the dining room and features gas cooking. There's also an interior laundry & utility room on the opposite side of the kitchen. While most of the home retains its classic 1920s style and allure, the home has some modern conveniences, too, including central heat. There's also a long driveway on the left side of the house, with ample room to park several cars. And a portion of the former garage still stands at the end of the driveway, which, with a little extra work, could even serve as a handy carport for the time being.

3rd Party Synd. Remarks: Welcome home to this beautifully renovated 4 bedroom 2 bath in one of Oakland's highly sought-after neighborhoods, Maxwell Park. Enjoy cooking in this large remodeled chef's kitchen with LG stainless steel appliances (it sings to you when the timer is up), custom high-end cabinetry, quartz countertops and a functional peninsula island with a butcher block top. This open and spacious floor plan give the home a bright and airy feel that everyone loves. Tons of upgrades have been meticulously selected by the homeowner, including luxurious bathrooms with elegant finishes, modern luxury plank vinyl flooring, copper plumbing, french drain around the entire home, backyard fencing, sewer lateral compliance and so much more! The lower level features a custom paint job in the family room with a separate entrance, a master bedroom with a spa-like bathroom and laundry room closet. The sliding doors open up to an expansive terraced backyard great for entertaining, gardening and relaxing. The possibilities for outdoor living are endless. Convenient location near local shopping, dining, and entertainment. Don't miss out on the chance to make this amazing property your own!
